$ Stellarium API: core.setObserverLocation

`core.setObserverLocation()` makes → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium travel to a given location on Earth or a planet.

code {
core.setObserverLocation(
   longitude    ,
   latitude     ,
   altitude     ,
   duration     , // optional   , default = 1
   name         , // optional   , default = ""
   planet         // optional(?), default = ""
);
code }

  Although the documentation specifies `planet` to be optional, it seems that at least when `core.setObserverLocation` is called for the first time, it needs to be set to a value.

{ Example

  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/setObserverLocation.ssc||

  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/img/setObserverLocation.png||

}
